### Minimal reproduce step

1、In class OpFindNewest, first, execute the method [readEntryComplete] [checkFirst] logic, if the condition [condition.apply(entry)] executes successfully, set the searchPosition=lastPosition and lastMatchedPosition=position, then execute find() method.

2、In the find() method, if cursor is not null, call cursor.hasMoreEntries(searchPosition).Even if there are still messages later searchPosition, if the message is acked, the method [cursor.hasMoreEntries(searchPosition)] may still return false.

3、If the method [cursor.hasMoreEntries(searchPosition)] return false, will return lastMatchedPosition directly.

4、In this case, it will return earliest position.


In my opinion, when querying the position based on the timestamp, the construction method of the cursor in the class OpFindNewest with null should be used


### What did you expect to see?

The position closest to provided timestamp

### What did you see instead?

The earliest position

